\s1 Jeremiah decided to stay with Gedaliah  
\p
\v 1  \add The soldiers from Babylonia\add* \w captured|strong="H3947"\w* \w me|strong="H7971"\w* \w and|strong="H3063"\w* \w many|strong="H7227"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H1931"\w* \w from|strong="H4480"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="H3389"\w* \w and|strong="H3063"\w* \add other places in\add* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*. \w They|strong="H3068"\w* \add planned to\add* \w take|strong="H3947"\w* \w us|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* Babylon. \w So|strong="H4480"\w* \w they|strong="H3068"\w* fastened chains around \w our|strong="H3068"\w* wrists \w and|strong="H3063"\w* \w took|strong="H3947"\w* \w us|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w Ramah|strong="H7414"\w* \add town north of Jerusalem\add*. \w While|strong="H1961"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w*, \w I|strong="H1697"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w released|strong="H7971"\w*. \add This is how it happened\add*:  
\v 2  \add Nebuzaradan,\add* \w the|strong="H3947"\w* \w captain|strong="H7227"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3947"\w* \add king’s\add* bodyguards, \add found that I was there\add*. \w He|strong="H3068"\w* \w summoned|strong="H3947"\w* \w me|strong="H3947"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w me|strong="H3947"\w*, “\w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H3068"\w* \w would|strong="H3068"\w* cause \w this|strong="H2088"\w* \w land|strong="H4725"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* experience \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w disaster|strong="H7451"\w*.  
\v 3 \w And|strong="H3068"\w* \w now|strong="H1961"\w* \w he|strong="H3588"\w* \w has|strong="H3068"\w* \w caused|strong="H1961"\w* \w it|strong="H6213"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w happen|strong="H1961"\w*. \w He|strong="H3588"\w* \w has|strong="H3068"\w* \w done|strong="H6213"\w* \w just|strong="H1697"\w* \w what|strong="H1697"\w* \w he|strong="H3588"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \add that he would do\add*, \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w people|strong="H3808"\w* \w sinned|strong="H2398"\w* \w against|strong="H1696"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w refused|strong="H3808"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w obey|strong="H8085"\w* \w him|strong="H6213"\w*.  
\v 4 \w But|strong="H7200"\w* \w today|strong="H3117"\w* \w I|strong="H3117"\w* am \w going|strong="H3212"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w take|strong="H7760"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* chains \w off|strong="H5921"\w* \w your|strong="H3605"\w* \w wrists|strong="H3027"\w* \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w release|strong="H6605"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w*. \w If|strong="H2009"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* want \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w come|strong="H3212"\w* \w with|strong="H5921"\w* \w me|strong="H6440"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* Babylon, \add that will be fine\add*. \w I|strong="H3117"\w* \w will|strong="H5869"\w* \w take|strong="H7760"\w* \w care|strong="H3027"\w* \w of|strong="H3117"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w*. \w But|strong="H7200"\w* \w if|strong="H2009"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* \w do|strong="H7489"\w* \w not|strong="H2308"\w* want \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w come|strong="H3212"\w* \w with|strong="H5921"\w* \w me|strong="H6440"\w*, \w do|strong="H7489"\w* \w not|strong="H2308"\w* \w come|strong="H3212"\w*. \add Stay here\add*. \w Look|strong="H7200"\w*, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w entire|strong="H3605"\w* country \w is|strong="H3117"\w* available; \w you|strong="H6440"\w* \w can|strong="H7200"\w* choose \w whatever|strong="H3605"\w* \w part|strong="H4480"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* want \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w go|strong="H3212"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w*. \w You|strong="H6440"\w* \w can|strong="H7200"\w* \w go|strong="H3212"\w* \w wherever|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* \w wish|strong="H2896"\w*.” \add Then he took the chains off my wrists\add*.  
\v 5 \w He|strong="H3605"\w* said, “\w If|strong="H1121"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \add decide to\add* \w stay|strong="H3427"\w* here, \w go|strong="H3212"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w*. \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Babylon \w appointed|strong="H6485"\w* \w him|strong="H5414"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w governor|strong="H6485"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*. \add You will be allowed to\add* \w stay|strong="H3427"\w* here \w with|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \add that he is governing\add*. \w But|strong="H3808"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w can|strong="H3808"\w* \w do|strong="H5869"\w* \w whatever|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w want|strong="H6485"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w*.”  
\p \w Then|strong="H7971"\w* Nebuzaradan \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* \w me|strong="H5414"\w* \w some|strong="H7227"\w* food \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w some|strong="H7227"\w* money, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* \w allowed|strong="H5414"\w* \w me|strong="H5414"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \w go|strong="H3212"\w*.   
\p
\v 6 \w I|strong="H1121"\w* returned \w to|strong="H1121"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w at|strong="H3427"\w* \w Mizpah|strong="H4708"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w I|strong="H1121"\w* \w stayed|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* Judah \w with|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H8432"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w who|strong="H5971"\w* \w still|strong="H3427"\w* \w remained|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H8432"\w* land.   
\s1 Many people returned to Judah  
\p
\v 7 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \add Israeli\add* \w soldiers|strong="H2428"\w* \add who had not surrendered to the army of Babylonia\add* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* roaming around \w in|strong="H4428"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w countryside|strong="H7704"\w*. \w Then|strong="H8085"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w leaders|strong="H8269"\w* \w heard|strong="H8085"\w* someone say \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Babylon \w had|strong="H4428"\w* \w appointed|strong="H6485"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w to|strong="H8085"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w governor|strong="H8269"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w very|strong="H1992"\w* \w poor|strong="H1803"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \add who were still in Judah\add*, \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w had|strong="H4428"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w been|strong="H6485"\w* \w taken|strong="H1540"\w* \w to|strong="H8085"\w* Babylon.  
\v 8 \w So|strong="H1992"\w* \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w went|strong="H1121"\w* \add to talk\add* \w to|strong="H1121"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w at|strong="H1436"\w* \w Mizpah|strong="H4708"\w*. \add Those who went included\add* \w Ishmael|strong="H3458"\w* \w the|strong="H3458"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Nethaniah|strong="H5418"\w*, \w Johanan|strong="H3110"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Jonathan|strong="H3129"\w* \w the|strong="H3458"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Kareah|strong="H7143"\w*, \w Seraiah|strong="H8304"\w* \w the|strong="H3458"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Tanhumeth|strong="H8576"\w*, \w the|strong="H3458"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Ephai|strong="H5778"\w* \w from|strong="H1121"\w* Netophath, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Jezaniah|strong="H3153"\w* \w from|strong="H1121"\w* Maacah, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3458"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H1121"\w* \w who|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w with|strong="H1121"\w* \w them|strong="H1992"\w*.  
\v 9 \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w solemnly|strong="H7650"\w* \w promised|strong="H7650"\w* \w that|strong="H4428"\w* \w the|strong="H5647"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H1121"\w* \w from|strong="H1121"\w* \w Babylonia|strong="H3778"\w* \w would|strong="H4428"\w* \w not|strong="H3372"\w* harm \w them|strong="H3427"\w*. \w He|strong="H4428"\w* said, “\w Do|strong="H3190"\w* \w not|strong="H3372"\w* \w be|strong="H1121"\w* \w afraid|strong="H3372"\w* \w to|strong="H1121"\w* \w do|strong="H3190"\w* \w things|strong="H3372"\w* \w for|strong="H3427"\w* \w them|strong="H3427"\w*. \w Stay|strong="H3427"\w* \add here\add* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w this|strong="H4428"\w* land \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w do|strong="H3190"\w* \w things|strong="H3372"\w* \w for|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H5647"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Babylon. \w If|strong="H1121"\w* \w you|strong="H5647"\w* \w do|strong="H3190"\w* \w that|strong="H4428"\w*, \w things|strong="H3372"\w* \w will|strong="H4428"\w* \w go|strong="H3190"\w* \w well|strong="H3190"\w* \w for|strong="H3427"\w* \w you|strong="H5647"\w*.  
\v 10 \w As|strong="H6440"\w* \w for|strong="H6440"\w* \w me|strong="H6440"\w*, \w I|strong="H2005"\w* \w will|strong="H5892"\w* \w stay|strong="H3427"\w* \add here\add* \w at|strong="H3427"\w* \w Mizpah|strong="H4709"\w* \w to|strong="H6440"\w* \w be|strong="H5892"\w* \w your|strong="H7760"\w* representative \w to|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \add officials from\add* \w Babylonia|strong="H3778"\w* \w who|strong="H3427"\w* \w come|strong="H5892"\w* \w to|strong="H6440"\w* \add talk with\add* \w us|strong="H6440"\w*. But \w you|strong="H6440"\w* should \add return to your towns, and eat the things that are produced on your land\add*. \w Harvest|strong="H7019"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* grapes \w and|strong="H5892"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w fruit|strong="H7019"\w* \add that ripen in\add* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* ◄\w summer|strong="H7019"\w*/hot season► \w and|strong="H5892"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* olives, \add make wine and olive oil,\add* \w and|strong="H5892"\w* store \w it|strong="H7760"\w*.”   
\p
\v 11 \w Then|strong="H1571"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Jews|strong="H3064"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w had|strong="H4428"\w* fled \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w Moab|strong="H4124"\w*, \w Ammon|strong="H5983"\w*, Edom, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* \add nearby\add* countries \w heard|strong="H8085"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* say \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Babylon \w had|strong="H4428"\w* \w allowed|strong="H5414"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* few \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \add to remain\add* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w he|strong="H3588"\w* \w had|strong="H4428"\w* \w appointed|strong="H6485"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w be|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w governor|strong="H6485"\w*.  
\v 12 \w So|strong="H7725"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \add began to\add* \w return|strong="H7725"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*. \w They|strong="H8033"\w* \w stopped|strong="H7725"\w* \w at|strong="H7725"\w* \w Mizpah|strong="H4708"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \add talk with\add* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w*. \w Then|strong="H7725"\w* \add they went to various places in Judea, and\add* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* harvested \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w great|strong="H3966"\w* \w amount|strong="H7235"\w* \w of|strong="H4725"\w* grapes \w and|strong="H3063"\w* \w summer|strong="H7019"\w* \w fruit|strong="H7019"\w*.   
\s1 The plot to kill Gedaliah  
\p
\v 13  \add Some time later,\add* \w Johanan|strong="H3110"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \add other\add* \w leaders|strong="H8269"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Israeli \w soldiers|strong="H2428"\w* \add who had not surrendered to the army of Babylonia\add* came \w to|strong="H1121"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w at|strong="H1436"\w* \w Mizpah|strong="H4708"\w*.  
\v 14 \w They|strong="H3588"\w* said \w to|strong="H7971"\w* \w him|strong="H5221"\w*, “Do \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w know|strong="H3045"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w Baalis|strong="H1185"\w*, \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w Ammon|strong="H5983"\w* \add people-group\add*, \w has|strong="H4428"\w* \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* \w Ishmael|strong="H3458"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Nethaniah|strong="H5418"\w* \w to|strong="H7971"\w* assassinate \w you|strong="H3588"\w*?” \w But|strong="H3588"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w did|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* believe \w what|strong="H3045"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* said.   
\p
\v 15 Later \w Johanan|strong="H3110"\w* talked \w with|strong="H3045"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w privately|strong="H5643"\w*. \w He|strong="H3605"\w* said, “\w Allow|strong="H4994"\w* \w me|strong="H4994"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w go|strong="H3212"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* murder \w Ishmael|strong="H3458"\w* \w secretly|strong="H5643"\w*. \w It|strong="H3045"\w* \w would|strong="H4100"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* \w good|strong="H4100"\w* [RHQ] \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w allow|strong="H4994"\w* \w him|strong="H5221"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w come|strong="H3212"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* murder \w you|strong="H3605"\w*! \w If|strong="H1121"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w killed|strong="H5221"\w*, \w what|strong="H4100"\w* \w will|strong="H5315"\w* happen \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Jews|strong="H3063"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w have|strong="H3045"\w* returned \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w this|strong="H3045"\w* area? \w They|strong="H3808"\w* \w will|strong="H5315"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* \w scattered|strong="H6327"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w remain|strong="H3808"\w* \w in|strong="H3212"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w* \w will|strong="H5315"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* \w killed|strong="H5221"\w*!”   
\p
\v 16 \w But|strong="H3588"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w Johanan|strong="H3110"\w*, “\add No\add*, \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H1121"\w* \w not|strong="H6213"\w* allow \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w do|strong="H6213"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w*. \add I think that\add* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w lying|strong="H8267"\w* \w about|strong="H1697"\w* \w Ishmael|strong="H3458"\w*.”   
\c 41  
\s1 Gedaliah was murdered  
\p
\v 1 \w Ishmael|strong="H3458"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* member \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w*’s \w family|strong="H2233"\w*. \w He|strong="H8033"\w* \w had|strong="H1961"\w* \w been|strong="H1961"\w* \w one|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* Zedekiah’s important officials. \w In|strong="H4428"\w* October \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w that|strong="H4428"\w* \w year|strong="H7637"\w*, \w he|strong="H8033"\w* \w went|strong="H4428"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w Mizpah|strong="H4709"\w* \w with|strong="H3899"\w* \w ten|strong="H6235"\w* \w other|strong="H3162"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \add talk with\add* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w*. \w While|strong="H1961"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* eating \w together|strong="H3162"\w*,  
\v 2 \w Ishmael|strong="H3458"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5221"\w* other \w ten|strong="H6235"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* jumped \w up|strong="H6965"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w with|strong="H4428"\w* \w their|strong="H1961"\w* \w swords|strong="H2719"\w* \w they|strong="H5221"\w* \w killed|strong="H5221"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w*—\w the|strong="H5221"\w* \w man|strong="H1121"\w* whom \w the|strong="H5221"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Babylon \w had|strong="H1961"\w* \w appointed|strong="H6485"\w* \w to|strong="H4191"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w their|strong="H1961"\w* \w governor|strong="H6485"\w*!  
\v 3 \w Ishmael|strong="H3458"\w* \add and the other men\add* \w also|strong="H3458"\w* \w killed|strong="H5221"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Jews|strong="H3064"\w* \w and|strong="H8033"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H4421"\w* \w from|strong="H1961"\w* \w Babylonia|strong="H3778"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w with|strong="H4421"\w* \w Gedaliah|strong="H1436"\w* \w at|strong="H4421"\w* \w Mizpah|strong="H4709"\w*.   
